<paragraph blockId="36.[192,1441,539,1012]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,336,539,563]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Definition.</emphasis>
A close sister genus to 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[606,883,540,564]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Moeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[606,687,540,563]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Moeris</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[896,949,540,564]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Geyer, [1832]" authorityName="Geyer" authorityYear="1832" box="[1044,1377,539,564]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Talides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striga">
<emphasis box="[1044,1209,539,563]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Talides striga</emphasis>
Geyer, [1832]
</taxonomicName>
). Not in the same clade as 
<taxonomicName authority="Scudder, 1872" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1872" box="[445,716,572,596]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lerema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[445,537,572,595]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Lerema</emphasis>
Scudder, 1872
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[732,786,572,596]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith, 1797" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1797" box="[885,1213,571,596]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="accius">
<emphasis box="[885,1056,571,595]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Papilio accius</emphasis>
Smith, 1797
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Tigasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1233,1322,572,595]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Tigasis</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[283,337,604,628]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[436,816,603,628]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Tigasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zalates">
<emphasis box="[436,615,603,627]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Tigasis zalates</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
) or its subjective synonym 
<taxonomicName authority="Hayward, 1942" authorityName="Hayward" authorityYear="1942" box="[1146,1440,603,628]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Alerema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1146,1248,603,627]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Alerema</emphasis>
Hayward, 1942
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[200,254,636,660]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Hayward, 1942" authorityName="Hayward" authorityYear="1942" box="[352,734,635,660]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Alerema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeteria">
<emphasis box="[352,543,635,659]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Alerema aeteria</emphasis>
Hayward, 1942
</taxonomicName>
treated as junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bell, 1930" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Phlebodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[1219,1440,635,659]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Phlebodes simplex</emphasis>
Bell, 1930
</taxonomicName>
), where species from this genus were placed previously (
<figureCitation box="[991,1121,668,692]" captionStart-0="Figure 11" captionStart-1="Figure 12" captionStartId-0="29.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionStartId-1="31.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox-0="[195,1438,214,1295]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1440,214,1295]" captionTargetId-0="figure@29.[194,1442,213,1296]" captionTargetId-1="figure@31.[192,1440,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId-0="29" captionTargetPageId-1="31" captionText-0="Figure 11. Nuclear genome and Z chromosome trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." captionText-1="Figure 12. Mitochondrial genome and COI barcode trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677257" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677259" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3677257/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3677259/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Fig. 11–12</figureCitation>
). Keys to J.44.10 or J.41.6. in 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[225,389,699,723]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans (1955)</bibRefCitation>
. Genitalia illustrated by Bell in his fig. 9 (
<bibRefCitation author="Bell" box="[909,1029,700,724]" firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref26665" refString="Bell, E. L. 1942. New genera and new species of neotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). American Museum Novitates 1205: 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1942">Bell 1942</bibRefCitation>
). Distinguished from its relatives by a combination of the following characters: uncus undivided, narrowing to a point; in ventral view: uncus sides slightly concave, gnathos arms widely apart, crescent-shaped, the same length as uncus, forming an φ together with it; saccus short, about the length of uncus, penis stout; harpe shorter than 1/3 of valva, slightly upturned, finely serrated at the distal margin, with a small tooth near ampulla, separated from it by a small notch; antennae longer than half of costa, checkered; wings produced; narrow complete stigma on forewing from base of vein CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[815,824,907,921]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">1</subScript>
to vein 1A+2A in males; hindwing below greenishochreous with a postdiscal irregular row of indistinct pale blotch-like spots. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly1019.13.1:C3748G, aly208.17.4:G1754C, aly1475.19.1:A667G, aly 
<date box="[228,350,987,1011]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" value="1041-11-05">1041.11.5</date>
:G116G (not A), aly1294.15.2:A1078A (not T), aly272.12.6:A338A (not G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="36.[192,1440,1033,1089]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,1033,1057]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a feminine noun in the nominative singular, and denotes that all three species placed in this genus have “virid” in their names.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[192,1440,1110,1166]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,432,1110,1134]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[495,548,1111,1135]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Weeks, 1901" authorityName="Weeks" authorityYear="1901" box="[658,1065,1110,1134]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridenex">
<emphasis box="[658,899,1110,1134]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Pamphila viridenex</emphasis>
Weeks, 1901
</taxonomicName>
, which is a very close relative, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hayward, 1940" authorityName="Hayward" authorityYear="1940" box="[246,664,1142,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Oeonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subviridis">
<emphasis box="[246,466,1142,1166]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Oeonus subviridis</emphasis>
Hayward, 1940
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[192,823,1188,1212]" box="[192,823,1188,1212]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,1188,1212]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe Moncina A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Warren, A. D. &amp; J. R. Ogawa &amp; A. V. Z. Brower" box="[647,819,1188,1212]" journalOrPublisher="Phylogenetic relationships of subfamilies and circumscription of tribes in the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea). Cladistics" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" pagination="642 - 676" part="24" refId="ref28580" refString="Warren, A. D., J. R. Ogawa, and A. V. Z. Brower. 2008. Phylogenetic relationships of subfamilies and circumscription of tribes in the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea). Cladistics 24 (5): 642 - 676." type="journal article" year="2008">Warren, 2008</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
